Company Overview of RMB Investors Trust - RMB Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
RMB Investors Trust - RMB Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by RMB Capital Management, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the dividend paying value stocks of large-cap companies. The fund employs fundamental analysis with a top-down stock picking approach focusing on factors such as potential for sustained operating and revenue growth, product leadership and strong management teams that focus on enhancing shareholder value, companies with histories of paying regular dividends, and securities that that seem to be poised to benefit ...
RMB Investors Trust - RMB Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by RMB Capital Management, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the dividend paying value stocks of large-cap companies. The fund employs fundamental analysis with a top-down stock picking approach focusing on factors such as potential for sustained operating and revenue growth, product leadership and strong management teams that focus on enhancing shareholder value, companies with histories of paying regular dividends, and securities that that seem to be poised to benefit from restructuring or similar business changes to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index Total Return. The fund was formerly known as Burnham Investors Trust - Burnham Fund. RMB Investors Trust - RMB Fund was formed on February 13, 1961 and is domiciled in the United States.
