Funds and solutions - Overview
RMB core performance linked investment accounts

                RMB’s various performance linked investment accounts use a combination of alternative assets and equities, to provide an above average long-term real rate of return. These products differ in terms of structure, asset allocation, capital guarantee (if any), flexibility, instrument selection and liquidity parameters.
                
RMB core ETFs and ETNs

Unlike traditional Collective Investment Scheme (‘unit trust’) investments, RMB’s  Exchange Traded  Funds (ETFs) and Exchange Traded Notes (ETNs), are traded on the Johannesburg  Stock Exchange. In contrast to  traditional actively managed funds, they are passively managed - the performance  is index-linked and allocations are rules-based. The goal is to replicate the  performance of the index, rather than to strive for outperformance.

For more information on ETFs visit our RMB ETF microsite.

For more information on ETNs visit our RMB ETN microsite.
Bespoke solutions

RMB also offers bespoke investment solutions to meet your objectives in terms of liquidity, capital security, investment horizon and diversification. An experienced team with access to the extensive array of financial instruments across Rand Merchant Bank and the broader FirstRand Group, have the necessary experience, skills, tools and appetite for this unique area of specialisation to create bespoke investment solutions. A minimum investment size is applicable. 
